In summary, we have conducted controlled N-body simulations and shown that a core-collapsed SIDM halo could explain the high density of the GD-1 stellar stream perturber. For progenitor halos from the cosmological simulation of a Milky Way analog, the required self-interacting cross section σ/m ≳ 30 cm2 g−1 for ~108 M⊙ halos with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
